b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Cleanvoice is best suited for podcast post production, cleaning up recorded audio, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Soundraw, meanwhile, shines for video creators needing background music, royalty free music production, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, Cleanvoice describes itself as \"AI removes filler words, mouth sounds, and dead air.\" Soundraw, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI music generator for royalty-free background tracks.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Cleanvoice** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (4 vs 1), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Soundraw is a poor choice — far from it. Soundraw excels in its own right, particularly for video creators needing background music and royalty free music production.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent filler word removal, go with Cleanvoice. If fully royalty-free matters more to you, Soundraw is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
